context: The demographics of the <b5_0>British Isles<b5_0/> today are characterised by a generally high density of population in <a0_0>England<a0_0/>, which accounts for almost <a1_0><b8_0>80<b8_0/>%<a1_0/> of the total population of the islands. The largest urban area by far is the <b6_0><b7_0>Greater London Urban Area<b7_0/><b6_0/> with <a2_0>9 million<a2_0/> inhabitants.
